    {
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq",
      "url": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq",
      "inLanguage": "en-AU",
      "isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#webpage"
      },
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q1",
          "name": "What are the benefits?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q1-a",
            "text": "- Gives you time to consider your options and gather evidence and documentation to understand your position better."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q2",
          "name": "What are the risks?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q2-a",
            "text": "- If you do not take some action in response to the allegations of infringement in a timely way, the person alleging infringement may decide to escalate the issue and, for example, commence a legal action.\n- If you have received a letter of demand (or cease and desist letter), the other party may expect a response within a set period of time: see Receiving a letter of demand.\n- If you are actually infringing the other party's IP rights and you continue to do so while you decide what to do, then your ongoing infringement (particularly after you were made aware) could result in the other party being able to claim additional compensation if they start legal action against you."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q3",
          "name": "What are the possible outcomes?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q3-a",
            "text": "- The other party may give up and decide not to escalate the issue.\n- The other party chooses to escalate the dispute.\n- You decide to take action -- for example, by sending a reply, seeking legal advice, or starting legal action (including where the other party has made unjustified threats of infringement action against you (also referred to as 'groundless threats' in copyright law)."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q4",
          "name": "What might the costs be?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q4-a",
            "text": "This option does not necessarily involve upfront costs. However, you may choose to consult an IP lawyer or IP attorney to assess your situation and provide you with advice on your options and they will charge a fee."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q5",
          "name": "How much time might be involved?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q5-a",
            "text": "This will depend on your situation. It can take some time to research the identity of the other party and assess the strength of their claims before deciding what to do. You may also want to speak to an IP lawyer or IP attorney to get some advice on your options."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q6",
          "name": "How much is this used?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q6-a",
            "text": "Most businesses will take some time to evaluate the situation before deciding what to do."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q7",
          "name": "Who can use this?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q7-a",
            "text": "- Anyone accused of infringing IP, particularly where the claim seems unfounded\n- People who want time to gather evidence and obtain legal advice before making a move."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q8",
          "name": "Who's involved?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q8-a",
            "text": "- The person or business alleging infringement\n- You\n- (Optional) An IP lawyer or IP attorney who can help you with assessing the situation and advise you on your options."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q9",
          "name": "What do you need to proceed?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "@id": "https://ipfirstresponse.ipaustralia.gov.au/options/choose-not-respond-immediately#faq#q9-a",
            "text": "This will depend on what you decide to do.  \n\nTo evaluate the situation before deciding, it is recommended that you carefully consider: \n\n- the allegations of infringement that have been made against you\n- whether the allegations of infringement have merit\n- what relevant IP rights you might have\n- what demands the other party has made and when they might expect a reply\n- whether to seek advice from an IP lawyer or IP attorney."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
